<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,1984,2009]" lastBlockId="65.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="65" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
This genus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1833" box="[315,436,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Torymidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Torymidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grissell" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[452,678,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Torymidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Microdontomerinae">Microdontomerinae</taxonomicName>
) is known to be represented in asphodel seeds by a single hitherto 
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="description">
undescribed species. It was reared in abundance as a parasitoid of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Delvare &amp; Escolà &amp; Stojanova &amp; Benoit &amp; Lecomte &amp; Askew" authorityYear="2019" box="[900,1161,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Bruchophagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gijswijti">
<emphasis box="[900,1161,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Bruchophagus gijswijti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in seeds of 
<taxonomicName box="[1298,1436,151,176]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Asphodelus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fistulosus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">A. fistulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Antoni Ribes, who prepared the following description not long before his death.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
